er this could be explained by changes in the 'nature of the solution medium' at high sugar concentrations — where water can no longer be treated as a simple solvent. The dissertation is a window into early 20th century enzyme chemistry before molecular biology as a field existed. He was also a WW1 veteran. (Columbia University dissertation)","body":"Chandler Dymick Ingersoll earned a doctorate from Columbia University's Faculty of Pure Science, writing a dissertation on 'The Hydrolysis of Sucrose by Invertase at High Sugar Concentrations.' The work investigated how the enzyme invertase breaks down sucrose, specifically at concentrations where conventional kinetic models broke down — addressing the work of Michaelis and Menten on enzyme velocity constants.","number":1}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Chandler Dymick Ingersoll","first_name":"Chandler","last_name":"Ingersoll","middle_name":"Dymick","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://images.findagrave.com/photos/2020/281/216441007_27c3015b-34ce-402e-9b8b-5174c5ea9732.jpeg"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"chandler-ingersoll-1897"},"X01674":{"id":"X01674","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"tags":[],"sources":[],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":1,"marriages":[{"marriage_number":1,"spouse_id":"HD1877","children_ids":["HD2837","HD2838"],"date_year":1925}],"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1899,"month":7,"day":10,"city":"Chicago","county":"Cook County","state":"Illinois","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1984,"month":3,"day":17,"county":"Westchester County","state":"New York","c